This is a gist to apply for the Junior Software Engineer position at EasyBroker.  I created a solution in Ruby to read properties from the API. The code has a client to get the data and a printer to show the titles. I used standard libraries and Object Oriented Programming principles.  The solution includes:  easybroker_client.rb : Connects to the API and handles pagination. property_printer.rb : Prints the titles of the properties. test_properties.rb : A unit test for the printer. run.rb : The script to execute the program. To run the code:  Install minitest: gem install minitest Run the tests: ruby test_properties.rb Run the program: ruby run.rb
